title: Art in America-From Colonial Days through XIX Century
description:
Art in America: From Colonial Days through the Nineteenth Century
Crowell-Collier Press | 1969 | ISBN: 0027677702 | English | 200 pages | PDF | 29.2 MB

America's first artists painted signs and decorated coffins and coaches for a living. To earn extra money they painted portraits of their wealthier neighborsâ€” rather primitive paintings whose spare, linear quality is much admired today. The first American architects were carpenters and masons who built from memory, adapting Old World modes to New World needs and improvising techniques to suit available materials
